FBIS4-21771 "jptot014__l94071" JPRS-TOT-94-014-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 28 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA IRAQ Two UN Guards Wounded in Ambush; Government Blamed Two UN Guards Wounded in Ambush; Government Blamed Kurd Radio Report NC2803180494 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan in Arabic 1500 GMT 28 Mar 94 NC2803180494 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan in Arabic 1500 GMT 28 Mar 94 Arabic BFN [Text] A UN vehicle was the target of an attack by agents of the Iraqi regime at the [name indistinct] checkpoint yesterday as the vehicle was traveling from Irbil to Mosul. It was carrying four people, two of them UN policemen. An employee of the IRC [abbreviation given in English] Organization named [words indistinct] told KURDISTAN NWAY newspaper that nine armed men opened fire at the vehicle at the Iraqi regime's checkpoint, seriously wounding the passengers. Eyewitnesses said that the nine armed men, who were dressed in Kurdish costumes, fled to the nearby Iraqi regime camps.
